text.tspan: return.connectedSpawners // get the right spawner with currentChunkFromTrack
ChunkSpawner: spawns main chunks in the world
Keeps track of chunk number, forward distance offset and height offset for each chunk
RailSpawner: spawns rails that then spawn other terrain chunks around
Keeps track of terrain slope direction from the rails
takes terrain chunk heights based on ChunkGenerator's height
ChunkGenerator: spawns other generators for this specific horizontal chunk
Keeps track of its altitude and all of its connected spawners
Can have everything refactored into the RailSpawner and only keep track of some variables
ConnectedSpawner: The spawners that randomly generate the actual terrain parts
Keeps track of the previous connected spawner,
the type of terrains that it can spawn depending on the terrains to the side and previous chunk terrains
Actual Terrain: the actual terrain parts that would be spawned by the ConnectedSpawners
Keeps track of the PossibleChunks that can be spawned by other ConnectedSpawners that are just
other actual terrains like itself and the slope type on each side that can match with the RailSpawner
Terrain details: the terrain details are the actual vegetation, rocks, NPC's and trees that would spawn
on top of each actual terrain. This can potentially be another script attached to the actual terrains so
the spawning of things on top of the terrain would look better and align the objects with the surface of the terrain
int ChunkAltitude // ranging from minAltitudeSteps to max
used to know if the rails can spawn any slopes leading to higher or lower
chunk Y position and rail slope type are the ones to be used to actually calculate next chunk height
requiredAltitudeSteps (of the selected chunk to spawn)
